==English==

===Etymology===
{{AS.}} ''[[hræfter]]''.

===Adverb===
'''hereafter'''
# In time to come; in some future time or state.
#:'''''Hereafter''' he from war shall come. Dryden.''

===Noun===
'''hereafter'''
# A future existence or state.
#:'' 'Tis Heaven itself that points out an '''hereafter'''.''  -Addison.

